  Name: The Human Brain
  Description: The human brain is the command center of the nervous system. It processes
    sensory information, regulates vital body functions, and controls thought, memory,
    and emotion. To handle these complex tasks, the brain is divided into two main
    halves, known as the left and right hemispheres.
